    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-13T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-13T14:00:00-05:00" n="580"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/3059: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-13T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 13, 1935—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 13—5:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>653. The Secretariat circulated this afternoon: the text of the Fronco-British
                    proposals for a settlement of the Italo-Abyssinian dispute;<note n="18"
                        xml:id="d580fn18">League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official
                        Journal</hi>, January 1936, p. 39.</note> a communications from the
                    Abyssinian Government to the <pb facs="0812" n="710" xml:id="pg_710"/> Secretary
                    General dated today in regard to the proposals;<note n="19" xml:id="d580fn19"
                        >League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official Journal</hi>, January 1936,
                        p. 41.</note> the reply of the Secretary General to the latter.</p>
                <p>I am informed that full texts are being telegraphed by the American press
                    agencies here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
